body:
*@fmatosqg commented on Apr 20, 2018, 5:15 AM UTC:*

## Steps to Reproduce

*   Edit pubspec.yaml
*   Immediately click `get packages`
*   Notice that it won't read the latest changes

If you `cmd+s` before clicking the expected result happens.

AS 3.1.1 with flutter plugin 23.2.2 and flutter beta 2.

*This issue was moved by [devoncarew](https://github.com/devoncarew) from [flutter/flutter#16786](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/16786).*

*@zoechi commented on Apr 20, 2018, 5:42 AM UTC:*

You don't have disabled auto-save? [https://stackoverflow.com/questions/28946013/how-to-disable-auto-save-save-in-android-studio](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/28946013/how-to-disable-auto-save-save-in-android-studio)

*@fmatosqg commented on Apr 20, 2018, 7:14 AM UTC:*

Definitely no, I haven't used cmd+s in Intellij for years :)
If I wait a few seconds or switch screens I get expected behavior.
We should verify this behavior and make sure we save the pubspec contents when calling the flutter packages commands.
@stevemessick : can you remind me why you reverted this fix?  Are you looking at this one?

The save needs to be done in a write context. This code was invoked from
too many places.
